article.headline: Cornell 69, Colgate 56
article.story: ITHACA, N.Y. (AP) -- Andrew Gore scored 16 points to lead Cornell to a 69-56 win over Colgate Tuesday night. The Big Red (2-2) snapped a four-game losing streak against Colgate (2-2), and won on their home floor for the first time in eight outings against the Raiders. Andrew Naeve had 14 points and nine rebounds and Jason Hartford added 13 points and six rebounds to the Big Red attack. Kyle Roemer was Colgate's leading scorer with 20 points, while sophomore Kyle Chones tallied his first career double-double with a career-high 16 points and 10 rebounds. Jon Simon added 12 points for the Raiders. The Big Red was leading 34-25 at halftime. In the second half, Cornell increased its advantage over the Raiders to 20 points, before Colgate managed to cut the deficit in half with just over one minute remaining. The Raiders out-rebounded the Big Red, 30-28.
